### SQL: Enforce AAL2 for Supabase Users with Verified MFA Factors

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/guides/auth/auth-mfa.mdx

This restrictive SQL policy for Supabase tables requires 'aal2' for users who have at least one verified MFA factor. Users without verified MFA factors are allowed 'aal1' or 'aal2'. It queries `auth.mfa_factors` to determine MFA enrollment status.

```sql
create policy "Policy name."
  on table_name
  as restrictive -- very important!
  to authenticated
  using (
    array[(select auth.jwt()->>'aal')] <@ (
      select
          case
            when count(id) > 0 then array['aal2']
            else array['aal1', 'aal2']
          end as aal
        from auth.mfa_factors
        where ((select auth.uid()) = user_id) and status = 'verified'
    ));
```

